        <abstract> 
<p>JVC is willing to translate [<hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>], especially because of his conviction that progress of biology depends on proving CD’s theory.</p>  
<p>Ernst Haeckel’s book [<hi rend="italic">Generelle Morphologie</hi> (1866)] will do mischief because EH is so immoderate. Suggests CD tell EH that he has done him a bad service. CD is the only one to whom EH would listen.</p> 
        </abstract>
